{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1747,"text":"My talk today is about something"},{"time":3785,"text":"maybe a couple of you have already heard about."},{"time":6118,"text":"It's called the Arab Spring."},{"time":8452,"text":"Anyone heard of it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10350,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13475,"text":"So in 2011, power shifted,"},{"time":18220,"text":"from the few to the many,"},{"time":20863,"text":"from oval offices to central squares,"},{"time":24618,"text":"from carefully guarded airwaves"},{"time":27611,"text":"to open-source networks."},{"time":30298,"text":"But before Tahrir was a global symbol of liberation,"},{"time":35082,"text":"there were representative surveys"},{"time":37066,"text":"already giving people a voice"},{"time":40056,"text":"in quieter but still powerful ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43549,"text":"I study Muslim societies around the world at Gallup."},{"time":48381,"text":"Since 2001,"},{"time":50865,"text":"we've interviewed hundreds of thousands of people --"},{"time":54246,"text":"young and old, men and women,"},{"time":56021,"text":"educated and illiterate."},{"time":58161,"text":"My talk today draws on this research"},{"time":61664,"text":"to reveal why Arabs rose up"},{"time":65597,"text":"and what they want now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68614,"text":"Now this region's very diverse,"},{"time":71796,"text":"and every country is unique."},{"time":73781,"text":"But those who revolted"},{"time":75431,"text":"shared a common set of grievances"},{"time":78370,"text":"and have similar demands today."},{"time":81547,"text":"I'm going to focus a lot of my talk on Egypt."},{"time":84398,"text":"It has nothing to do with the fact that I was born there, of course."},{"time":87764,"text":"But it's the largest Arab country"},{"time":91348,"text":"and it's also one with a great deal of influence."},{"time":94763,"text":"But I'm going to end by widening the lens to the entire region"},{"time":98747,"text":"to look at the mundane topics"},{"time":101564,"text":"of Arab views of religion and politics"},{"time":104347,"text":"and how this impacts women,"},{"time":107532,"text":"revealing some surprises along the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111304,"text":"So after analyzing mounds of data,"},{"time":115433,"text":"what we discovered was this:"},{"time":117901,"text":"Unemployment and poverty alone"},{"time":121140,"text":"did not lead to the Arab revolts of 2011."},{"time":125734,"text":"If an act of desperation by a Tunisian fruit vendor"},{"time":128817,"text":"sparked these revolutions,"},{"time":130535,"text":"it was the difference between what Arabs experienced"},{"time":134535,"text":"and what they expected"},{"time":136915,"text":"that provided the fuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138748,"text":"To tell you what I mean,"},{"time":140149,"text":"consider this trend in Egypt."},{"time":142331,"text":"On paper the country was doing great."},{"time":145307,"text":"In fact, it attracted accolades"},{"time":148164,"text":"from multinational organizations"},{"time":150616,"text":"because of its economic growth."},{"time":152682,"text":"But under the surface was a very different reality."},{"time":155331,"text":"In 2010, right before the revolution,"},{"time":159081,"text":"even though GDP per capita"},{"time":161232,"text":"had been growing at five percent for several years,"},{"time":164331,"text":"Egyptians had never felt worse about their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168831,"text":"Now this is very unusual,"},{"time":171099,"text":"because globally we find that, not surprisingly,"},{"time":174400,"text":"people feel better as their country gets richer."},{"time":178015,"text":"And that's because they have better job opportunities"},{"time":180798,"text":"and their state offers better social services."},{"time":184211,"text":"But it was exactly the opposite in Egypt."},{"time":186599,"text":"As the country got more well-off,"},{"time":189331,"text":"unemployment actually rose"},{"time":191749,"text":"and people's satisfaction"},{"time":194399,"text":"with things like housing and education plummeted."},{"time":200336,"text":"But it wasn't just anger at economic injustice."},{"time":204626,"text":"It was also people's deep longing for freedom."},{"time":212000,"text":"Contrary to the clash of civilizations theory,"},{"time":216266,"text":"Arabs didn't despise Western liberty,"},{"time":219802,"text":"they desired it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221754,"text":"As early as 2001,"},{"time":224503,"text":"we asked Arabs, and Muslims in general around the world,"},{"time":227976,"text":"what they admired most about the West."},{"time":230905,"text":"Among the most frequent responses"},{"time":233572,"text":"was liberty and justice."},{"time":235924,"text":"In their own words to an open-ended question"},{"time":239090,"text":"we heard, \"Their political system is transparent"},{"time":242006,"text":"and it's following democracy in its true sense.\""},{"time":245207,"text":"Another said it was \"liberty and freedom"},{"time":247206,"text":"and being open-minded with each other.\""},{"time":249938,"text":"Majorities as high as 90 percent and greater"},{"time":254573,"text":"in Egypt, Indonesia and Iran"},{"time":256991,"text":"told us in 2005"},{"time":259674,"text":"that if they were to write a new constitution"},{"time":263873,"text":"for a theoretical new country"},{"time":267239,"text":"that they would guarantee freedom of speech"},{"time":269564,"text":"as a fundamental right,"},{"time":271974,"text":"especially in Egypt."},{"time":274058,"text":"Eighty-eight percent said moving toward greater democracy"},{"time":278040,"text":"would help Muslims progress --"},{"time":280606,"text":"the highest percentage of any country we surveyed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284823,"text":"But pressed up against these democratic aspirations"},{"time":288523,"text":"was a very different day-to-day experience,"},{"time":291624,"text":"especially in Egypt."},{"time":293790,"text":"While aspiring to democracy the most,"},{"time":297308,"text":"they were the least likely population in the world"},{"time":302055,"text":"to say that they had actually voiced their opinion"},{"time":305782,"text":"to a public official in the last month --"},{"time":308156,"text":"at only four percent."},{"time":311839,"text":"So while economic development made a few people rich,"},{"time":316607,"text":"it left many more worse off."},{"time":319605,"text":"As people felt less and less free,"},{"time":323191,"text":"they also felt less and less provided for."},{"time":326940,"text":"So rather than viewing their former regimes"},{"time":330690,"text":"as generous if overprotective fathers,"},{"time":334124,"text":"they viewed them as essentially prison wardens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338325,"text":"So now that Egyptians have ended Mubarak's 30-year rule,"},{"time":342741,"text":"they potentially could be"},{"time":344908,"text":"an example for the region."},{"time":347574,"text":"If Egypt is to succeed"},{"time":349296,"text":"at building a society based on the rule of law,"},{"time":352763,"text":"it could be a model."},{"time":355615,"text":"If, however,"},{"time":356940,"text":"the core issues that propelled the revolution aren't addressed,"},{"time":361364,"text":"the consequences could be catastrophic --"},{"time":365074,"text":"not just for Egypt,"},{"time":366308,"text":"but for the entire region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369580,"text":"The signs don't look good, some have said."},{"time":373208,"text":"Islamists, not the young liberals that sparked the revolution,"},{"time":378041,"text":"won the majority in Parliament."},{"time":380640,"text":"The military council"},{"time":382311,"text":"has cracked down on civil society and protests"},{"time":386626,"text":"and the country's economy continues to suffer."},{"time":389994,"text":"Evaluating Egypt on this basis alone, however,"},{"time":394759,"text":"ignores the real revolution."},{"time":399387,"text":"Because Egyptians are more optimistic"},{"time":401566,"text":"than they have been in years,"},{"time":404013,"text":"far less divided on religious-secular lines"},{"time":407785,"text":"than we would think"},{"time":409101,"text":"and poised for the demands of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413016,"text":"Whether they support Islamists or liberals,"},{"time":415967,"text":"Egyptians' priorities for this government are identical,"},{"time":419311,"text":"and they are jobs, stability and education,"},{"time":422067,"text":"not moral policing."},{"time":424400,"text":"But most of all,"},{"time":425468,"text":"for the first time in decades,"},{"time":426899,"text":"they expect to be active participants, not spectators,"},{"time":430649,"text":"in the affairs of their country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432950,"text":"I was meeting with a group of newly-elected parliamentarians"},{"time":436966,"text":"from Egypt and Tunisia"},{"time":438501,"text":"a couple of weeks ago."},{"time":440033,"text":"And what really struck me about them"},{"time":442811,"text":"was that they weren't only optimistic,"},{"time":448000,"text":"but they kind of struck me as nervous,"},{"time":450842,"text":"for lack of a better word."},{"time":452193,"text":"One said to me,"},{"time":453482,"text":"\"Our people used to gather in cafes to watch football\" --"},{"time":456405,"text":"or soccer, as we say in America --"},{"time":459422,"text":"\"and now they gather to watch Parliament.\""},{"time":463805,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":467159,"text":"\"They're really watching us,"},{"time":469381,"text":"and we can't help but worry"},{"time":473368,"text":"that we're not going to live up to their expectations.\""},{"time":475888,"text":"And what really struck me"},{"time":477396,"text":"is that less than 24 months ago,"},{"time":479588,"text":"it was the people that were nervous"},{"time":481839,"text":"about being watched by their government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484921,"text":"And the reason that they're expecting a lot"},{"time":487771,"text":"is because they have a new-found hope for the future."},{"time":491375,"text":"So right before the revolution"},{"time":493161,"text":"we said that Egyptians had never felt worse about their lives,"},{"time":496638,"text":"but not only that, they thought their future would be no better."},{"time":500938,"text":"What really changed after the ouster of Mubarak"},{"time":504171,"text":"wasn't that life got easier."},{"time":506005,"text":"It actually got harder."},{"time":508112,"text":"But people's expectations for their future"},{"time":511205,"text":"went up significantly."},{"time":513005,"text":"And this hope, this optimism,"},{"time":515402,"text":"endured a year of turbulent transition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519748,"text":"One reason that there's this optimism"},{"time":523276,"text":"is because, contrary to what many people have said,"},{"time":527007,"text":"most Egyptians think things really have changed in many ways."},{"time":531189,"text":"So while Egyptians were known"},{"time":534023,"text":"for their single-digit turnout"},{"time":537490,"text":"in elections before the revolution,"},{"time":539758,"text":"the last election had around 70 percent voter turnout --"},{"time":543590,"text":"men and women."},{"time":545589,"text":"Where scarcely a quarter believed in the honesty of elections in 2010 --"},{"time":550503,"text":"I'm surprised it was a quarter --"},{"time":552184,"text":"90 percent thought that this last election was honest."},{"time":556296,"text":"Now why this matters"},{"time":557874,"text":"is because we discovered a link"},{"time":561040,"text":"between people's faith in their democratic process"},{"time":565274,"text":"and their faith that oppressed people"},{"time":569123,"text":"can change their situation"},{"time":571640,"text":"through peaceful means alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":585731,"text":"Now I know what some of you are thinking."},{"time":588152,"text":"The Egyptian people,"},{"time":589785,"text":"and many other Arabs who've revolted and are in transition,"},{"time":593635,"text":"have very high expectations of the government."},{"time":597052,"text":"They're just victims of a long-time autocracy,"},{"time":601850,"text":"expecting a paternal state"},{"time":604067,"text":"to solve all their problems."},{"time":606446,"text":"But this conclusion would ignore"},{"time":610035,"text":"a tectonic shift taking place in Egypt"},{"time":613185,"text":"far from the cameras in Tahrir Square."},{"time":617201,"text":"And that is Egyptians' elevated expectations"},{"time":620867,"text":"are placed first on themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624234,"text":"In the country once known for its passive resignation,"},{"time":628401,"text":"where, as bad as things got,"},{"time":630267,"text":"only four percent expressed their opinion to a public official,"},{"time":633736,"text":"today 90 percent tell us"},{"time":637048,"text":"that if there's a problem in their community,"},{"time":639320,"text":"it's up to them to fix it."},{"time":641753,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":649446,"text":"And three-fourths"},{"time":651249,"text":"believe they not only have the responsibility,"},{"time":654080,"text":"but the power to make change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657050,"text":"And this empowerment"},{"time":659314,"text":"also applies to women,"},{"time":662246,"text":"whose role in the revolts"},{"time":663917,"text":"cannot be underestimated."},{"time":666068,"text":"They were doctors and dissidents,"},{"time":668469,"text":"artists and organizers."},{"time":670035,"text":"A full third of those who braved tanks and tear gas"},{"time":675168,"text":"to ask or to demand liberty and justice in Egypt"},{"time":680203,"text":"were women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681876,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":687519,"text":"Now people have raised some real concerns"},{"time":690208,"text":"about what the rise of Islamist parties means for women."},{"time":693874,"text":"What we've found about the role of religion in law"},{"time":698158,"text":"and the role of religion in society"},{"time":700674,"text":"is that there's no female consensus."},{"time":703660,"text":"We found that women in one country"},{"time":707843,"text":"look more like the men in that country"},{"time":709810,"text":"than their female counterparts across the border."},{"time":714474,"text":"Now what this suggests"},{"time":715992,"text":"is that how women view religion's role in society"},{"time":720059,"text":"is shaped more by their own country's culture and context"},{"time":725340,"text":"than one monolithic view"},{"time":727855,"text":"that religion is simply bad for women."},{"time":730692,"text":"Where women agree, however,"},{"time":734457,"text":"is on their own role,"},{"time":736040,"text":"and that it must be central and active."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738573,"text":"And here is where we see the greatest gender difference within a country --"},{"time":743691,"text":"on the issue of women's rights."},{"time":746441,"text":"Now how men feel about women's rights"},{"time":749041,"text":"matters to the future of this region."},{"time":752490,"text":"Because we discovered a link"},{"time":754524,"text":"between men's support for women's employment"},{"time":758526,"text":"and how many women are actually employed"},{"time":761725,"text":"in professional fields in that country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764909,"text":"So the question becomes,"},{"time":766373,"text":"What drives men's support for women's rights?"},{"time":770548,"text":"What about men's views of religion and law?"},{"time":777297,"text":"[Does] a man's opinion"},{"time":780182,"text":"of the role of religion in politics"},{"time":783067,"text":"shape their view of women's rights?"},{"time":786716,"text":"The answer is no."},{"time":787949,"text":"We found absolutely no correlation,"},{"time":790834,"text":"no impact whatsoever,"},{"time":792648,"text":"between these two variables."},{"time":795183,"text":"What drives men's support for women's employment"},{"time":798899,"text":"is men's employment,"},{"time":801783,"text":"their level of education"},{"time":804282,"text":"as well as a high score"},{"time":807067,"text":"on their country's U.N. Human Development Index."},{"time":811166,"text":"What this means"},{"time":812357,"text":"is that human development,"},{"time":815431,"text":"not secularization,"},{"time":817727,"text":"is what's key to women's empowerment"},{"time":820447,"text":"in the transforming Middle East."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824131,"text":"And the transformation continues."},{"time":827080,"text":"From Wall Street to Mohammed Mahmoud Street,"},{"time":830963,"text":"it has never been more important"},{"time":833020,"text":"to understand the aspirations"},{"time":835364,"text":"of ordinary people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837482,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839213,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}